Careers



Culture 
New College Graduates
Intern Program 










Help shape the future of technology at ESI.
If you're looking to make an impact, ESI is the place to consider. We are leaders in innovative technology.
ESI is a pioneer and leading supplier of world-class production laser systems that help its microtechnology customers achieve compelling yield and productivity gains. The company's industry-leading, application-specific products enhance electronic-device performance in three key sectors — semiconductors, passive components and electronic interconnect — by enabling precision fine-tuning of device micro-features in high-volume manufacturing environments. Founded in 1944, ESI is headquartered in Portland, Oregon.
If you are an experienced professional or an individual just beginning your career you'll have the opportunity to spend your working hours on challenging projects that help shape the future of technology. We provide a collaborative work environment where people enjoy what they do.
Explore the jobs we have to offer. 

Click to view ESI's Equal Opportunities & Affirmative Action Program and the Pay Transparency Nondiscrimination Provision.







CULTURE 








Our Mission
Develop, design and deliver lasers, laser-based systems and services that meet or exceed customer needs. 
Our Vision
Be seen by customers as the industry company of choice and premium value leader in laser-based micromachining applications across broad industry markets. 
Our Values 
Accountability: We take ownership and responsibility for delivering results that meet the needs of our customers, employees and shareholders. 
Creativity: Our passion for innovation is at the heart of who we are and what we do. 
Integrity: We operate with the highest level of ethics and integrity in all aspects of our business. 
People: We tackle complex challenges through teamwork and individual contributions - people are the key to our success. 
Quality: We embrace business processes that help to ensure high quality products and services are delivered to our customers. 







NEW COLLEGE GRADUATES








Join ESI and your learning continues. 
Now that you have completed your degree, your learning doesn’t stop. It continues. You will have an opportunity to take what you have gained in school and expand your knowledge by obtaining additional hands-on experience. ESI offers meaningful employment opportunities, career development possibilities and an environment that recognizes and balances personal and professional needs. Whether you're a current student or have graduated in the last 18 months, you may be eligible to be hired through our college recruitment program.







INTERN PROGRAM 








Gain hands-on real-world experience at ESI. 
Internships provide both you and ESI an opportunity to get to know each other. An ESI internship will help you gain hands-on real-world experience and develop practical skills that will assist you in your academic and career pursuits. We are looking for ambitious students involved in undergraduate and graduate level programs in engineering or business-related fields. Excellent communication and team-building skills, a former internship and relevant class or work experience are all advantages.
 







For industries facing material transformation challenges in production,  ESI applies unique process and engineering expertise to deliver a set of laser-based solutions that extend our customers’ processing capabilities beyond the limitations of mechanical.
See what it's like to be an ESI customer - contact an ESI Sales Expert today




















	MICROVIA DRILLING | Electro Scientific Industries Inc. (ESI) | New Products | Mar 2003 | Photonics Spectra
 


































