	Other-than-temporary impairment of cost method investments




	As of March 30, 2013, the Company had made a total investment in the equity of OmniGuide, Inc., of $9.0 million. The investment is accounted for as a cost method investment. In the second quarter of 2014, the Company invested an additional $5.0 million in OmniGuide Series F Preferred Stock. As this Series F Preferred Stock round of equity financing was priced below previous rounds, it was considered a triggering event and the Company recorded a


	$3.6 million


	 impairment charge of Series D and Series E investments at that time. In the fourth quarter of 2014, further triggering events were identified due to poor operating results through the end of the year combined with decreasing cash levels. As a result the Company performed an updated valuation of these investments and recorded an additional impairment of


	$6.1 million


	, for a total other-than-temporary impairment of


	$9.7 million


	 in 2014. Remaining carrying value of these cost method investments as of March 29, 2014 was $4.3 million.











