	10. Goodwill




	As of


	March 29, 2014


	 and as of


	March 30, 2013


	, the Company had


	$7.9 million


	 in goodwill comprised of


	$3.9 million


	 from the Eolite acquisition in 2013 and


	$4.0


	 million from the PyroPhotonics acquisition in 2011. We performed an annual goodwill impairment analysis during the fourth quarter of 2014 and determined that the fair value of our single reporting unit was greater than its carrying value. If at any time management determines that an impairment exists, we will be required to reflect the impaired value as part of operating income, which will result in a reduction in earnings and a corresponding reduction in our net asset value in the period such impairment is identified.






